Summarise each of the {n} numbered groups of memory snippets below. Each group represents one branch of a memory hierarchy; the summary you produce will be attached to that branch so the answering LLM can skim the tree and decide whether to drill deeper.

## Rules for each summary
- 2-4 sentences. Dense with facts, no filler.
- Preserve personal facts (degree, age, family, job, decisions, places, dates) and proper nouns (brands, people, products). A summary that omits these has FAILED.
- No preamble; don't repeat the group number; don't quote back the snippets.

## Output format
Return ONLY a JSON array of exactly {n} strings, in the same order as the numbered groups. No markdown fences, no trailing commentary, no keys — just the array.

## Groups
{numbered}
